    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-04-11T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-04-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="649"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d649">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 654.119/238a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-04-11">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 11, 1918</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3515. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName> [from
                    War Trade Board]:</p>
                <p>No. 29. We have cabled <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DEL1"
                        >Dresel</persName> our opinion that negotiations with Switzerland for lumber
                    and other commodities should be conducted at Berne rather than at Paris. Will
                    you please be guided accordingly.</p>
                <p>
                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_DEL1">Dresel</persName> suggests that
                    inter-Ally commission on lumber should go from Paris to Berne and should include
                    American representative. We approve of this suggestion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
